('business:1-6-business-growth:mcq:f065dd19', 'business', 'business:1-6-business-growth', '1.6 Business Growth', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following is NOT an example of organic growth?", "options": ["Increasing output", "Merging with a supplier", "Developing new products", "Gaining new customers"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct answer: B — Merging with a supplier. Merging with any other business is always external (inorganic) growth, regardless of whether it is a supplier, customer or rival. Options A, C, and D are all internal methods of growing the business from within."}'::jsonb)
